  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 emergency online education in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to reduce the digital gap of children and their families in our community by providing access to internet connection and technological devices in order to minimize school dropouts and learning loss due to the COVID-19 crisis. Colegio La Fontaine is closed since March 2020 but provides online education to its 174 students. In case the government of Colombia does not allow schools to reopen, we need to ensure that every single child keeps learning and developing skills at home.</narrative>
  </description>
